[[File:Desert Lizard icon.png|left]]
'''Desert lizards''' are [[Slayer monsters]] found in the [[Kharidian Desert]], requiring level 22 [[Slayer]] to kill. In order to kill a desert lizard, an [[ice cooler]] must be used when it has less than 5 [[Hitpoints]]. If an ice cooler is used on a desert lizard with 5 or more Hitpoints, the cooler will be consumed but have no effect. Players can buy the "[[Slayer Rewards#Unlock|Reptile freezer]]" perk from a [[Slayer master]] for 90 [[Slayer reward point|Slayer points]], which will automatically ice the desert lizard when it falls below 5 Hitpoints, provided that the player has an ice cooler in their inventory. 

The lizards are located south-east of the [[Shantay Pass]], across the [[River Elid]], roaming around south of the area where orange salamanders can be caught. The easiest route to get there is by taking a [[magic carpet]] ride to the temples of [[Uzer]], then heading south-west. Alternatively, players with access to [[fairy rings]] can use the code {{Fairycode|dlq}} to get to them faster.

The lizards are found in areas affected by [[desert heat]], so players are advised to bring a [[water]] source like [[waterskin]]s to avoid taking damage from the heat. Those with access to the fairy ring system can easily refill waterskins by re-entering [[Zanaris]] and using the water fountain located north of the fairy ring.

Although the task says "Desert lizard", any other lizards around the area are also counted toward the task.

Slaying one is a requirement for the [[Desert Diary#Medium|Medium Desert Diary]].

The final blow cannot be dealt by using [[Ancient Magicks]] [[ice spells]].

